==English==

===Etymology===
Latin.  Originally meant "head of hair".
Maybe from the persian root " kaisar " meaning head of the kings.

===Pronunciation===
*Latin {{IPA|/ˈkaisar/}}
*English (''rhotic'') {{IPA|/ˈsiːzər/}}
*English (''non-rhotic'') {{IPA|/ˈsiːzə/}}

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Caesar'''
# An ancient Roman family name, notably that of [[w:Julius Caesar|Gaius Iulius Caesar]]
# A title of [[Roman]] [[emperor]]s.

